data.description: Privacy and amenities abound in this classic Dutch Colonial home on a corner lot in Rolling Hills Subdivision!  This three bedroom home features plenty of privacy with a landscaped back yard including a wood deck, Invisible Fence system, raised-bed composting garden, and easy access to a nearby exercise trail per the sellers. Inside you'll be greeted with vintage parquet flooring in the entryway, with new knotted chestnut-style laminate flooring throughout the main level.  Also included on the main level is a rec room, half-bath, smart thermostat, eat-in kitchen, informal dining room, and a large living room with lots of natural light. Upstairs you'll find 3 bedrooms, one full and one half bath, as well as ample closet space. This two-owner home features lots of important updates including windows in 2000, a high-efficiency furnace with built-in humidifier in 2017, central air in 2019, a radon mitigation system in 2020, and new laminate flooring on the main level in 2021.  Per the sellers, the basement was waterproofed and foundation stabilized by MidAmerica Basement Systems in 2021 which includes a double sump pump with battery backup and whole-home dehumidifier. Inspections welcome, but property is being sold 'as is'. Check out this gem today! Owner is a licensed Realtor.
